OL,3,CMan threw vacuum cleaner and told
OL,4,Cpolice 'I hope your children get raped'
OL,6,FAppearing at Teesside Crown Court on
OL,7,FMonday (12 August), the defendant was
OL,8,Fjailed for 26 months having pleaded
OL,9,Fguilty to violent disorder and
OL,10,Fpossession of an offensive weapon.
OL,12,FRachel Masters, prosecuting, said
OL,13,FRogers was seen throwing bricks at
OL,14,Fpolice by an officer who later asked
OL,15,Fif he was okay, as he had blood on his
OL,16,FT-shirt.
OL,18,FRogers replied he had cut his hand
OL,19,Fthrowing rocks at the police, and
OL,20,F"would do it again."
